# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Comment regex if you want to share it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may get conflicts.
#   In that case, the lock file should be added to .gitignore.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   Refer to https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   Refer to https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/project/#commit-your-pdmlock-file-to-version-control
# pdm.lock

